quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  97,1,"Indeed, We sent this [Qur’an] down on the Night of Decree."
  97,2,"How do you know what the Night of Decree is?"
  97,3,"The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months."
  97,4,"On that night the angels and the Spirit [i.e., Gabriel] descend by their Lord’s permission with all decrees."
  97,5,"It is all peace until the break of dawn."
  98,1,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists were not going to desist [from disbelief] until there came to them clear proof,"
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah, reciting pure pages"
  98,3,"containing upright commandments."
  98,4,"Yet those who were given the Scripture did not disagree except after the clear proof came to them,"
  98,5,"although they were commanded only to worship Allah with sincere devotion to Him, being inclined to the true faith, and to establish prayer and give zakah; that is the true religion."
  98,6,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists will be in the fire of Hell, abiding therein forever. It is they who are the worst of creatures."
  98,7,"As for those who believe and do righteous deeds – it is they who are the best of creatures."